casebody.data:
GUSSIE REICHNER ET AL., PLAINTIFFS, v. SAMUEL T. DAVIDSON, DEFENDANT. Decided September 5, 1929.

Before Justices Trenchard, Kalisch and Lloyd.

For the applicant, Weinberger & Weinberger. For the respondent, Feder & Rinzler. Per Curiam.

We have examined with care the petition and find it to be without merit.

The result is that the application for a rehearing is denied.
